      <guid>http://katakurashohei.me/home/about/</guid>
      <description>I&amp;rsquo;m a 2nd year of a Master&amp;rsquo;s student in the Graduate School of Advanced Mathematical Sciences, Meiji University, advised by Prof. Keita Watanabe.
My research interest is human-computer interaction (HCI), especially personal fabrication. I design a relationship and interaction with fabrication machines by creating software and hardware systems. My research goal is to enable non-experts to create interactable and movable physical objects with 3D printing technologies.</description>
